		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message32822051">Just going to throw this out there, but I absolutely love Hyouka. And I'm not exactly sure why. <br />
<br />
Sure, mystery lovers, fans of Sherlock Holmes or Agatha Christie can love the references and the mysteries. As for me, I love spoilers, so the mystery aspect must not have hooked me. <br />
<br />
Yeah, the art is great, but I've seen plenty more anime with art just as good, or better. Besides, the art was just the typical KyoAni moe stuff, with transparent-like backgrounds, again, typical of KyoAni. <br />
<br />
Then again, maybe it's everything together_ friendship+mystery+great art. <br />
<br />
But so far, I think the biggest reason I love Hyouka is that it makes everyday life exciting. My favorite episode, the one in which Oreki shows Chitanda how to decipher a simple intercom announcement, showed not just the mystery, but also the thinking behind it. It almost encouraged me to find mysteries in my everyday life and solve them. The solutions were never really interesting, but the process getting there always kept me on my toes_ and for a person who loves spoilers, who looked up all the solutions to the mysteries on the Wikipedia summary before even finishing the first episode of each arc, the process, the proof that even normal life can be a lot of fun, probably got me the most.</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/animelist/einonymous&amp;sclick=1"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://myanimelist.net/signature/einonymous.png" /></a> </div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
