		  <td class="forum_boardrow1" style="border-width: 0px 1px 1px 1px;" valign="top"><div id="message32867047">To me, Hyouka is one of the most unbearable anime of all time. Visually exciting for a slice-of-life that takes place mostly in one room, the characters are what make this anime take a nosedive for me. The lead male seems like a masturbatory recreation of Kyon, and the lead female is so impossibly simplistic it makes the mystery aspect practically disappear. When a &quot;mystery&quot; arises you know our genius-in-disguise will supersleuth it out. He'll manage to trigger a series of impossible conclusions with the help of the only two supporting cast members. It's just frustrating to see Hyouka tagged as a mystery when it is certainly not. Clues are never more meaningful than their face value of being clues by definition. They simply lead the cast towards the inevitability that the mystery will be solved. For me, mystery is more than that. A good mystery reveals as much about the detective as it does about the narrative. That's where Hyouka falls flat. I really do enjoy the premise, but the execution makes me think KyoAni made this anime for I don't know... something... else...</div><div class="postActions"></div><div class="sig"><!--link--><a href="http://myanimelist.net/animelist/Detective&amp;sclick=1"><img class="userimg" data-src="http://cdn.myanimelist.net/signature/Detective.png" /></a> </div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
