The ending is not nearly as cathartic as I'd like, but it does indicate the significant development that has taken place. It is very subtle, but when you realise it's happening, it is beautiful...<!--quote--></div><br />
The last episode is probably one of my favourite episodes as it shows the very subtly but noticeable changes that have occured throughout the series. Purely by Oreki simply picking up the phone and agreeing to go out, not to mention those few last minutes where the Oreki and Chitanda shipping went completely insane only to have it fall victim of drowning in too many feels.<br />
<br />
<!--quote--><div class="quotetext"><strong>BigSimo said:</strong><!--quotesaid--><br><!--quote--><div class="quotetext"><strong>einonymous said:</strong><!--quotesaid--><br><br />
Yeah, the art is great, but I've seen plenty more anime with art just as good, or better. Besides, the art was just the typical KyoAni moe stuff, with transparent-like backgrounds, again, typical of KyoAni. <!--quote--></div><br />
I would argue that it has among the best/animation art of any tv series I've seen. Takemoto Yasuhiro is a master director, and his use of depth and lighting adds so much to the atmosphere and unique feel of the show. Out of curiosity - what are the shows you consider to have better animation? Stuff like Yuasa Masaaki's shows and the like can't really be compared to this though, they are so vastly different. I'd say something like Mushishi is of a similar quality as Hyouka though.<br />
But seriously, stuff like that scene in ep 1 with the vines and flowers entangling Oreki, and that scene later in the show where all the chibi Chintanda's surround Oreki with the &quot;kininarimasu, kininarimasu, etc etc&quot; - these are amazing.<!--quote--></div><br />
Not to mention the exquisite attention to detail with the backgrounds, and whilst the characters look similar they have very obvious character traits, which follow human anatomy, and we are able to distinguish between one another such as their eyes but the main characters all have different colour eyes - more typical of KyoAni now? I'm not really sure - Besides from their eyes, the colours of used within the anime aren't very bright and do well to fit the mystery aspect of the anime.</div><div class="postActions"></div></td>
		</tr></table></div><div class="forum_boardrowspacer">&nbsp;</div>
